data.name: Nebelung
data.description: The name Nebelung is German and means “creature of the mist,” a reference to the cat’s shimmering silvery-blue coat that seems to float over his body.

data.name: American Bobtail
data.description: Bobtailed cats, the result of a natural genetic mutation that causes a shortened tail, have appeared in various places over the centuries, from Japan to the Isle of Man

data.name: Chartreux
data.description: The Chartreux might well be compared to a mime, silent but communicative and sometimes silly

data.name: Japanese Bobtail
data.description: The Japanese Bobtail breed’s tell-tale characteristic is a short “bunny” tail that can be flexible or rigid, with one or more curves, angles or kinks.

data.name: Bengal Cats
data.description: The Bengal is highly active and highly intelligent.This makes him fun to live with, but he can sometimes be challenging.
